---- MODULE DieHarder  ----- (* Define module *)  ===== Module Definition Starts Here ========  (**************************************************************************)    CONSTANTS Jug, Capacity \* The set of all jug capacities.     Goal       *The goal amount to be measured by the process.)
VARIABLES LiquidLevel  /\ TLC will define this as a function from time-steps(nat numbers starting at zero)to liquid levels (subsets of Jug).   ===== Module Definition End Here ========  (* Define variables *)  ===========================================================================     Spec == []LiquidsAtTimeStep[0] = {})/\  (\E t \in Nat : LiquidLevel' [t+1 ] IN MCCapacity(Jug) /\ ((\A i,j: Jug |-> Cardinality{i} +Cardinality{( j)}=Goal )  ==== Specification Definition Starts Here ========  (* Define specification *)
===========================================================================     Invariants == []LiquidsAtTimeStep[t] SUBSET Capacity  /\ t \in Nat)   ======Invariant definition starts here ===========(*Define invariance*)      CONSTANTS Goal <- MCGoals, Jug< - MCLiqJug  ==== Define constants for TLC configuration ========
===========================================================================     NextState == []LiquidsAtTimeStep[t+1] = ((\E i \in Capacity: LiquidLevel [ t ] SUBSET {i} /\ Cardinality{(Cap - Difference{Subset(Jug,2), SubSet})}=Cardinality Jug)  ==== Define next state ========  (*Define the transition relation*)
===========================================================================     Config == ([]LiquidsAtTimeStep[0] = {} )/\  (\E t \in Nat : NextState [t+1 ] IN MCCapacity(Jug)) /\ (((\A i,j: Jug |-> Cardinality{i} +Cardinality{( j)}=Goal)))  ==== Define configuration for TLC ========  (*Define the specification*)
===========================================================================    THEOREM Config => []TypeOK    ====== Theorem definition starts here ===========(*Axiom to prove that our model is type correct *)  (**************************************************************************) ) ----- END OF MODULE DieHarder-----  ===== Module Ends Here ========  (*End of module*)
====